Sentencas: In this work, Pr-deficiency is presented here as an effective strategy to promote the electrochemical properties of PrxBaFe2O5+delta (PrxBF, x = 1.00, 0.97, 0.93, 0.90)
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The PrxBF cathode materials were prepared by a sol-gel method.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure results show that the PrxBF (x = 1.00) is double-perovskite phase with orthorhombic structure and the PrxBF (x = 0.97, 0.93, 0.90) is tetragonal perovskite structure.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introduction of Pr-deficiency in PrxBF oxides causes the decrease of oxygen content.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC values (30-850 C) for PrxBF are mainly concentrated between 15.29 and 15.95 x 10(-6) K-1.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In comparison to the parent PrxBaFe2O5+delta oxides, the Pr-deficiency cathodes significantly enhance the electrochemical catalytic activity while maintain the lower thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the series of PrxBF cathodes, the Pr0.93BF sample obtains the lowest polarization resistance.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The fitted result of impedance spectra for Pr0.93BF cathode indicates that the charge transfer process in the high frequency plays a more dominant role in the oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the Pr0.93BF electrode exhibits a good tolerance to CO2.
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power density of an anode supported single cell with Pr0.93BF cathode achieved 967 mW cm(-2) at 700 C. Preliminary results suggest that PrxBF oxides are expected to be promising candidates for cathode in SOFC.(c) 2022
Titulo: A-site deficient Fe-based double perovskite oxides PrxBaFe2O5+δ as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
